{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1425,"text":"I have never, ever forgotten the words of my grandmother"},{"time":6991,"text":"who died in her exile:"},{"time":9391,"text":"\"Son, resist Gaddafi. Fight him."},{"time":14256,"text":"But don't you ever turn"},{"time":17463,"text":"into a Gaddafi-like revolutionary.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":23586,"text":"Almost two years have passed"},{"time":25740,"text":"since the Libyan Revolution broke out,"},{"time":28556,"text":"inspired by the waves of mass mobilization"},{"time":33306,"text":"in both the Tunisian and the Egyptian revolutions."},{"time":38106,"text":"I joined forces with many other Libyans inside and outside Libya"},{"time":43206,"text":"to call for a day of rage"},{"time":45406,"text":"and to initiate a revolution against the tyrannical regime of Gaddafi."},{"time":51890,"text":"And there it was, a great revolution."},{"time":55923,"text":"Young Libyan women and men were at the forefront"},{"time":59623,"text":"calling for the fall of the regime,"},{"time":62807,"text":"raising slogans of freedom, dignity, social justice."},{"time":68023,"text":"They have shown an exemplary bravery"},{"time":71063,"text":"in confronting the brutal dictatorship of Gaddafi."},{"time":75130,"text":"They have shown a great sense of solidarity"},{"time":78645,"text":"from the far east to the far west to the south."},{"time":82129,"text":"Eventually, after a period of six months of brutal war"},{"time":88045,"text":"and a toll rate of almost 50,000 dead,"},{"time":93513,"text":"we managed to liberate our country and to topple the tyrant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98896,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":105145,"text":"However, Gaddafi left behind a heavy burden,"},{"time":109579,"text":"a legacy of tyranny, corruption and seeds of diversions."},{"time":116914,"text":"For four decades Gaddafi's tyrannical regime"},{"time":121215,"text":"destroyed the infrastructure as well as the culture and the moral fabric of Libyan society."},{"time":129664,"text":"Aware of the devastation and the challenges,"},{"time":133364,"text":"I was keen among many other women to rebuild the Libyan civil society,"},{"time":140147,"text":"calling for an inclusive and just transition"},{"time":143639,"text":"to democracy and national reconciliation."},{"time":146706,"text":"Almost 200 organizations were established in Benghazi"},{"time":150523,"text":"during and immediately after the fall of Gaddafi --"},{"time":153422,"text":"almost 300 in Tripoli."}]},{"cues":[{"time":156323,"text":"After a period of 33 years in exile, I went back to Libya,"},{"time":162273,"text":"and with unique enthusiasm,"},{"time":164490,"text":"I started organizing workshops"},{"time":166972,"text":"on capacity building, on human development of leadership skills."},{"time":171804,"text":"With an amazing group of women,"},{"time":174339,"text":"I co-founded the Libyan Women's Platform for Peace,"},{"time":178121,"text":"a movement of women, leaders, from different walks of life,"},{"time":182989,"text":"to lobby for the sociopolitical empowerment of women"},{"time":187590,"text":"and to lobby for our right"},{"time":189740,"text":"for equal participation in building democracy and peace."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194857,"text":"I met a very difficult environment in the pre-elections,"},{"time":200573,"text":"an environment which was increasingly polarized,"},{"time":204557,"text":"an environment which was shaped by the selfish politics of dominance and exclusion."},{"time":214025,"text":"I led an initiative by the Libyan Women's Platform for Peace"},{"time":218107,"text":"to lobby for a more inclusive electoral law,"},{"time":222241,"text":"a law that would give every citizen, no matter what your background,"},{"time":226706,"text":"the right to vote and run,"},{"time":229790,"text":"and most importantly to stipulate on political parties"},{"time":233941,"text":"the alternation of male and female candidates"},{"time":238656,"text":"vertically and horizontally in their lists,"},{"time":242040,"text":"creating the zipper list."},{"time":244873,"text":"Eventually, our initiative was adopted and successful."},{"time":251218,"text":"Women won 17.5 percent of the National Congress"},{"time":256990,"text":"in the first elections ever in 52 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261255,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":268006,"text":"However, bit by bit, the euphoria of the elections,"},{"time":274474,"text":"and of the revolution as a whole,"},{"time":278206,"text":"was fading out --"},{"time":279790,"text":"for every day we were waking up to the news of violence."},{"time":284256,"text":"One day we wake up to the news"},{"time":286490,"text":"of the desecration of ancient mosques and Sufi tombs."},{"time":289962,"text":"On another day we wake up to the news"},{"time":291757,"text":"of the murder of the American ambassador and the attack on the consulate."},{"time":296258,"text":"On another day we wake up to the news"},{"time":298340,"text":"of the assassination of army officers."},{"time":301857,"text":"And every day, every day we wake up with the rule of the militias"},{"time":307424,"text":"and their continuous violations of human rights of prisoners"},{"time":312274,"text":"and their disrespect of the rule of law."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316206,"text":"Our society, shaped by a revolutionary mindset,"},{"time":319742,"text":"became more polarized"},{"time":321703,"text":"and has driven away from the ideals and the principles --"},{"time":325381,"text":"freedom, dignity, social justice --"},{"time":328447,"text":"that we first held."},{"time":330147,"text":"Intolerance, exclusion and revenge"},{"time":334257,"text":"became the icons of the [aftermath] of the revolution."},{"time":339289,"text":"I am here today not at all to inspire you"},{"time":343939,"text":"with our success story of the zipper list and the elections."},{"time":348123,"text":"I'm rather here today to confess"},{"time":350324,"text":"that we as a nation took the wrong choice, made the wrong decision."},{"time":357106,"text":"We did not prioritize right."},{"time":359929,"text":"For elections did not bring peace and stability and security in Libya."},{"time":367323,"text":"Did the zipper list and the alternation between female and male candidates"},{"time":372623,"text":"bring peace and national reconciliation?"},{"time":375656,"text":"No, it didn't."},{"time":378073,"text":"What is it, then?"},{"time":380023,"text":"Why does our society continue to be polarized and dominated"},{"time":386206,"text":"with selfish politics of dominance and exclusion, by both men and women?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":393507,"text":"Maybe what was missing was not the women only,"},{"time":398026,"text":"but the feminine values of compassion, mercy and inclusion."},{"time":405230,"text":"Our society needs national dialogue and consensus-building"},{"time":409603,"text":"more than it needed the elections,"},{"time":411403,"text":"which only reinforced polarization and division."},{"time":415388,"text":"Our society needs the qualitative representation of the feminine"},{"time":421653,"text":"more than it needs the numerical, quantitative representation of the feminine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":427670,"text":"We need to stop acting as agents of rage and calling for days of rage."},{"time":434367,"text":"We need to start acting as agents of compassion and mercy."},{"time":439967,"text":"We need to develop a feminine discourse"},{"time":443601,"text":"that not only honors but also implements"},{"time":447734,"text":"mercy instead of revenge, collaboration instead of competition,"},{"time":456098,"text":"inclusion instead of exclusion."},{"time":459317,"text":"These are the ideals that a war-torn Libya"},{"time":462424,"text":"needs desperately in order to achieve peace."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465899,"text":"For peace has an alchemy,"},{"time":468083,"text":"and this alchemy is about the intertwining, the alternation"},{"time":475166,"text":"between the feminine and masculine perspectives."},{"time":478666,"text":"That's the real zipper."},{"time":480717,"text":"And we need to establish that existentially"},{"time":483766,"text":"before we do so sociopolitically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":486217,"text":"According to a Quranic verse"},{"time":489116,"text":"\"Salam\" -- peace -- \"is the word of the all-merciful God, raheem.\""},{"time":495617,"text":"In turn, the word \"raheem,\" which is known in all Abrahamic traditions,"},{"time":501352,"text":"has the same root in Arabic as the word \"rahem\" -- womb --"},{"time":506053,"text":"symbolizing the maternal feminine encompassing all humanity"},{"time":511887,"text":"from which the male and the female,"},{"time":514003,"text":"from which all tribes, all peoples, have emanated from."},{"time":519536,"text":"And so just as the womb entirely envelopes the embryo, which grows within it,"},{"time":528547,"text":"the divine matrix of compassion nourishes the entire existence."},{"time":536313,"text":"Thus we are told that \"My mercy encompasses all things.\""},{"time":541680,"text":"Thus we are told that \"My mercy takes precedence over my anger.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":547680,"text":"May we all be granted a grace of mercy."},{"time":552263,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":556083,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":558187,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}